The course gives an overview of ethical principles and codes of ethics for psychologists. The participants bring with them several analyses of their attitudes and beliefs about professional and ethical issues that form the study material for the course. The course will provide case vignettes and participant practicing of making use of seven steps in ethical decision making processObjectives/eesmärkid:  To give knowledge on ethical principles and regulations for psychologists (in science and practice) and  on ethical decision-making process to solve main ethical dilemmas and problems in professional work of psychologists.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Knowledge of ethical principles and code of conduct for psychologists working in practice and science.  Skills in ethical decision-making to solve ethical dilemmas in professional work of psychologists. Skills in identification of underlying values and value conflicts. Ability to distinguish ethical approach and action from unethical behaviour in professional psychology.
